reviewText: Enjoyable way to be a part of what's happening in Indian Country when you can't get out.  Also good to hear from the people of Indian Country.
Like it a lot. Fun to see what modern First Nations people are up to instead of the old stereotypes. Good hosts too.

It's intersting to see a positive spin on American Indians, rather than the usual negative stereotypes. I understand there are significant economic and social issues, but it's nice to also point out the folk who have worked hard and explored the creative industries. Representing the good side of contemporary Native life!
